China Stocks: China Cosco, Guilin Guanglu, Offshore Oil

-- B y   B l o o m b e r g   N e w s
-- 
2011-03-09T03:49:46Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-03-08/cosco-poly-shanghai-pharmaceuticals-china-equity-preview.html
Shares of the following companies
had unusual moves in  China  trading. Stock symbols are in
parentheses as of the 11:30 a.m. local-time break.  The Shanghai Composite Index, which tracks the bigger of
China’s stock exchanges, fell 4.2, or 0.1 percent, to 2,995.73.
The  CSI 300 Index (SHSZ300)  retreated 0.2 percent to 3,330.67.       Changjiang Securities Co. (000783 CH) jumped 7.6 percent to
12.91 yuan as it resumed trading today after a two-day
suspension. The brokerage said it raised 2.5 billion yuan ($381
million) from selling additional shares.  Guilin Guanglu Measuring Instrument Co. (002175 CH), a
manufacturer of electronic measuring equipment, added 1.7
percent to 15.51 yuan after saying it plans to raise up to 377
million yuan by selling up to 28 million shares in a private
share placement.  Offshore Oil Engineering Co. (600583 CH), a unit of the
country’s third-largest oil producer, gained 3.5 percent to 9.12
yuan. Shenyin & Wanguo Securities Co. raised its recommendation
on the stock to “outperform” from “hold,” saying Offshore
Oil will benefit from parent Cnooc Ltd.’s plan to boost
expenditure on deep-water exploration, Wang Sheng and Li Yamin,
analysts at the Shanghai-based brokerage, wrote in a report
today.  --Zhang Shidong. Editor: Richard Frost  To contact Bloomberg News staff for this story:
